'''Expander System Sweden AB''' is a Swedish company that designs, manufactures, and sells a pivot-pin system for commercial heavy machinery and equipment.  Their headquarters is in [[Ãtvidaberg]], [[Sweden]]. It was founded in 1986 by Everth and Roger Svensson. The Expander Group includes two subsidiaries, Expander Americas Inc, in the [[United States]], and Expander Deutschland GmbH, in [[Germany]].

The expander system consists of patented products that are intended to take the place of conventional pivot pins in [[heavy machinery]] and equipment. Conventional pivot pins may wear in a way that requires a costly repair process for pivot lug holes, called [[Boring (manufacturing)|line boring]]. The expander system uses expansion sleeves that can eliminate this wear problem.

